# Role: Frontend Developer

## Stack
React 18 + Vite + TypeScript + Tailwind CSS

## Conventions
- Components: `PascalCase` in `frontend/src/components/`
- Pages: `PascalCase` in `frontend/src/pages/`
- API calls: `camelCase` hooks in `frontend/src/api/`
- Constants: `UPPER_SNAKE_CASE`

## Required UI elements
- `AIGenerationStatus` — shows `idle | generating | complete | error` + current section name
- Cancel button during generation
- `compliance_score` badge on protocol viewer (0–100)
- Disclaimer: `"AI-Assisted. Requires qualified person review."` on every protocol view
- Watermark preview on export dialog

## Form validation rules (FR-02.6)
`phase IN ('I','II','III')` | `duration_weeks > 0` | `primary_endpoint` min 3 chars | `title` min 5 chars

## Screens (P0 first)
1. Protocol list (dashboard with status badges)
2. Create protocol form (3 steps: Template → Parameters → Criteria)
3. Protocol viewer (sidebar nav, section content, regenerate button)
4. Diff viewer (side-by-side, color-coded lines)

## Deviation constraint (NFR-06)
UI implementation must not deviate from `docs/functional-requirements.md` by more than:
- **15%** for standard UI functions (forms, lists, export, versioning)
- **25%** for AI generator UI (generation status, section display, compliance badge)

Cosmetic differences (colors, spacing, icons) are **not** counted as deviations.

## Checkpoints
- [ ] Form validates before submitting
- [ ] Generation progress shown in real time (polling)
- [ ] Export triggers file download
- [ ] All required FR fields present in UI (deviation ≤ 15% / 25%)
